      • withLocalQueueMessageSlots

        public SqsReadAheadQueue.Builder withLocalQueueMessageSlots(java.lang.Integer localQueueMessageSlots)
        Sets the number of slots, that is the message count limit, in the local queue that is used to buffer SQS messages. If no value is specified for localQueueMessageSlots, the local queue will be limited to the maximum number of in-flight messages that SQS imposes based on the type of queue:
        Standard
        120,000
        FIFO
        20,000
        Parameters:
        localQueueMessageSlots - maximum number of messages that will be buffered in the local queue
        Returns:
        this builder instance

      • withRegion

        public SqsReadAheadQueue.Builder withRegion(java.lang.String awsRegion)
        Sets the AWS region to use with the SQS connection.

        Note: Per AwsClientBuilder.withRegion(Regions), since Regions, at any point in time, may not include an element for every region, AwsClientBuilder suggests using AwsClientBuilder.withRegion(String) overload to specify the region. Consequently, this method declares awsRegion as String.

        Note: Per AWS API, specify either region or endpoint configuration, not both.

        Parameters:
        awsRegion - AWS region
        Returns:
        this builder instance
        See Also:
